The instructions for resolving a merge conflict currently have an incorrect path to the remote. Instead of &#x27;origin&#x27; the &#x27;user/repo&#x27; is shown. For example:

{{git merge --no-ff -m &#x27;Merged in bacon ([PR#1|https://bitbucket.org/site/master/pull-requests/1])&#x27; remotes/mbertrand999/blah/bacon}}

Should be

{{git merge --no-ff -m &#x27;Merged in bacon ([PR#1|https://bitbucket.org/site/master/pull-requests/1])&#x27; remotes/origin/bacon&#x27;}}

